{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Uw6Yaw9ympomqvpvHt2YAq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification\n**Files reviewed:** parser.ts, parser-keywords.ts, index.ts, AGENTS.md, verify-parser.test.ts, types.ts\n**Tests:** 3875 passed (62 in parser test file, up from 59)\n**Coverage:** 96.86% overall, all 158 files above 80% floor\n**Story status:** updated to `verifying`\n\n### Fixes applied\n\n1. **HIGH — `unit-testable` legacy tag not matched by regex** (`parser.ts` line 88): Added `unit-testable` to `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex. `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` had the mapping but the regex silently rejected the tag. Added corresponding test.\n\n2. **HIGH — Unsafe type assertion in `parseVerificationTag`** (`parser.ts` line 102): Added runtime validation against `TIER_HIERARCHY` before casting. If a value somehow passes the regex but isn't a known tier, it now returns `null` instead of producing an invalid `VerificationTier`.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — No test for unknown/invalid tag values** (`verify-parser.test.ts`): Added test proving `<!-- verification: unknown-value -->` returns null.\n\n4. **MEDIUM — No test for empty string input to `classifyTier`** (`verify-parser.test.ts`): Added test confirming empty string returns `test-provable`.\n\n5. **MEDIUM — No test for `unit-testable` legacy backward compat** (`verify-parser.test.ts`): Added test confirming `<!-- verification: unit-testable -->` maps to `test-provable`.\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex did not include `unit-testable` despite `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` having a mapping for it — backward compat was silently broken for this legacy value. Fixed.\n- HIGH: `parseVerificationTag` used `as VerificationTier` cast without runtime validation — could produce invalid tier if regex and type definition drift apart. Fixed with `TIER_HIERARCHY.includes()` guard.\n- MEDIUM: Missing test coverage for edge cases (empty string, unknown tags, unit-testable compat). Fixed with 3 new tests.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `TEST_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS` contains very short/broad keywords (`'type'`, `'export'`, `'function'`) that risk false-positive classification. Mitigated by priority ordering but inherently fuzzy. Story spec explicitly requires these keywords.\n- `ENVIRONMENT_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS` contains `'database'` which overlaps semantically with `DB_KEYWORDS` in `classifyAC`. A simple DB mock test would be classified as `environment-provable` tier. Design trade-off.\n- `RUNTIME_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS` keyword `'http'` overlaps with `API_KEYWORDS` — different classification dimensions but maintenance risk if someone assumes they should align.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None at per-file level (all files above 80%, overall 96.86%)\n- `parser.ts` line 196 (the `warn` call for empty AC description) is only covered when running the broader test suite, not from `verify-parser.test.ts` alone — acceptable since the full suite covers it.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `parseStoryACs` only parses numbered ACs (`1. Given...`) but the project's own story files use checkbox format (`- [x] AC1: ...`). Pre-existing limitation, not introduced by this story.\n- The keyword-based classification approach is inherently fuzzy. No scoring or weighting — first keyword match wins. Adequate for current use but may need rethinking if more tiers or keywords are added.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story status set to `verifying`.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 9, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 4, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite run (~15 lines shown), coverage check with per-file detail (~30 lines shown), codeharness coverage (~6 lines)\n- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: Read of parser.ts lines 96-103 was partially redundant with the full file read earlier (needed to confirm exact line numbers for edit). 4 Glob calls to find the workflow file could have been 2 (checked both _bmad and .claude separately, then narrowed)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af67e8629d261dc15 (use SendMessage with to: 'af67e8629d261dc15' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 58187\ntool_uses: 39\nduration_ms: 261829</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ab04accf-ff7f-4190-b6e9-807078c1f112","uuid":"f026dfad-10e5-4b61-99bb-62fd0dac8b82","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:38:56.370Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`\n\nMANDATORY — Also end your response with a `## Token Report` section:\n- Total tool calls: N\n- By tool: Bash: X, Read: Y, Edit: Z, Grep: W, Write: V, other: N\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): command (~N lines each)\n- Files read: N un