{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014sVno1hZqdxUSaBWkD4iEB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verify (2026-03-27T08:20Z)\n     4→\n     5→Tier A validation — proof existed with 10/10 PASS. Quick validation pass.\n     6→\n     7→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — review (2026-03-27T08:25Z)\n     8→\n     9→**Bugs found:**\n    10→- HIGH: Unsafe `as StackName` type cast in `dockerfile-generator.ts` masking type safety — FIXED\n    11→- MEDIUM: Double `apt-get update` layer in Rust+Bevy Dockerfile output — FIXED\n    12→- MEDIUM: Unquoted Python dist filename in COPY instruction (`env.ts:162`) — NOT FIXED\n    13→\n    14→**Tech debt:**\n    15→- 14 stale `mockDetectStack` call sites in `verify-env.test.ts`\n    16→- No logging when `getStackProvider()` returns undefined\n    17→\n    18→## Token Report\n    19→- Total tool calls: 20\n    20→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    21→- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n    22→\n    23→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — code-review (2026-03-27T09:35Z)\n    24→\n    25→**Bugs found and fixed:**\n    26→- HIGH: Subdirectory stack path not resolved before passing to provider — Bevy detection would silently fail for non-root stacks\n    27→- MEDIUM: Missing DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive — apt installs could hang on interactive prompts\n    28→- MEDIUM: Uncovered !provider and !section branches (66.66% branch coverage before fix)\n    29→- MEDIUM: env.ts at 305 lines (extra blank line), over NFR1 300-line limit\n    30→\n    31→**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n    32→- verify-env.test.ts still mocks dead detectStack import\n    33→- Multi-stack Dockerfile creates redundant apt-get update per provider section\n    34→- env.ts at 304 lines still over 300-line NFR1 limit\n    35→- Story Dev Agent Record claims 12 generator tests but actual count was 9\n    36→\n    37→**Coverage:** 96.87% overall, all 157 files above 80% floor\n    38→\n    39→## Token Report\n    40→- Total tool calls: 24\n    41→- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 12, Edit: 6, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    42→- Files read: 14 unique, 16 total reads\n    43→\n    44→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — code-review-2 (2026-03-27T13:55Z)\n    45→\n    46→No new bugs found. Previous HIGH/MEDIUM fixes verified solid. Coverage 97.45%, all files above 80% floor. 3856 tests passing. Status advanced to verifying.\n    47→\n    48→**LOW items not fixed:** fragile push() pattern in generator, no Docker syntax validation test, long line in env.ts.\n    49→\n    50→## Token Report\n    51→- Total tool calls: 22\n    52→- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 0\n    53→- Files read: 12 unique, 13 total reads\n    54→- Redundant operations: None\n    55→\n    56→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verify (2026-03-27T14:00Z)\n    57→\n    58→ALL_PASS (10/10 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, tests, coverage all passed.\n    59→\n    60→## Token Report\n    61→- Total tool calls: 24\n    62→- By tool: Bash: 15, Read: 5, Grep: 4, Write: 2\n    63→- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n    64→- Redundant operations: Second coverage run could have reused first output\n    65→\n    66→### 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification — create-story (2026-03-27T14:15Z)\n    67→\n    68→**Problems:** Epic 16 has no dedicated epics file — definition comes from tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md instead of standard epics document.\n    69→**Workarounds:** Used tech spec as authoritative source for story definitions.\n    70→**Risks:** 300-line limit for parser.ts is tight (278 lines, adding ~30 net).\n    71→**Observations:** Story 16-1 already modified parser.ts to add working tier derivation; 16-2 is cleanup/simplification.\n    72→\n    73→## Token Report\n    74→- Total tool calls: 16\n    75→- By tool: Read: 9, Grep: 2, Glob: 3, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n    76→- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads\n    77→- Redundant operations: None\n    78→\n    79→### 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification — code-review (2026-03-27T10:40Z)\n    80→\n    81→**Bugs found:**\n    82→- HIGH: `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex did not include `unit-testable` — backward compat silently broken. Fixed.\n    83→- HIGH: `parseVerificationTag` used unsafe `as VerificationTier` cast without runtime validation. Fixed with guard.\n    84→- MEDIUM: Missing test coverage for edge cases (empty string, unknown tags, unit-testable compat). 3 new tests added.\n    85→\n    86→**LOW not fixed:** Broad keywords risk false-positive classification. Keyword overlap between dimensions.\n    87→\n    88→## Token Report\n    89→- Total tool calls: 18\n    90→- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 9, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 4, Skill: 1\n    91→- Files read: 9 unique, 10 total reads\n    92→\n    93→### 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification — verify (2026-03-27T10:50Z)\n    94→\n    95→ALL_PASS (12/12 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build passed, 62 parser tests passing, parser-keywords.ts at 100% coverage. `codeharness verify` flagged `coverage_met` state flag (harness-level, not story-level). 5 test failures in unrelated modules (pre-existing).\n    96→\n    97→## Token Report\n    98→- Total tool calls: 14\n    99→- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 4, Grep: 1, Write: 1\n   100→- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n   101→- Redundant operations: npm test run 3 times (could have been 1 with tee)\n   102→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FTS4KLBTcQswfu36heJGP7","session_id":"ab04accf-ff7f-4190-b6e9-807078c1f112","uuid":"ab1e3282-6e86-4ad5-964d-dd09f5a83593","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:57:42.004Z"}
