: Run `codeharness stats --save` to generate the cost report. Read `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCRITICAL: The session issues log contains `## Token Report` sections from each subagent. Aggregate these to understand WHERE tokens were spent inside subagents (not just the parent). Look for:\n- Which subagent phases had the most tool calls?\n- Which subagents read the same files repeatedly?\n- Which Bash commands produced the largest outputs?\n- What redundant operations were reported?\nInclude this subagent-level breakdown in the cost analysis section.\n\nSession context: Loop #8, started 2026-03-27T10:31:08Z, 30-minute budget. One story completed: 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification (ready-for-dev → done). Note: story was already developed in a previous session — this session did code review + verification only. Also fixed stale sprint-state.json entries for 14-5, 14-6, 16-1 (were stuck at 'review' despite being committed as done).\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — which stories were attempted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report and token reports\n4. **What went well**\n5. **What went wrong**\n6. **Lessons learned**\n7. **Action items**\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md.\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"af51f7030c9b730fe","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective written to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md` (appended as Session 4).\n\n**Summary of findings:**\n\n- **1 story completed:** 16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification (create-story → code-review → verify → done)\n- **3 stale state entries fixed:** 14-5, 14-6, 16-1 corrected from \"review\" to \"done\"\n- **Session cost:** $9.99 across 75 API calls\n- **Code review caught 2 HIGH bugs:** broken regex (backward compat silently broken) and unsafe type cast (no runtime validation)\n- **Waste rate:** ~4% (2 redundant test runs out of 48 subagent calls)\n- **Recurring issue:** State drift flagged for the 4th consecutive session — needs a reconciliation mechanism at session start\n- **Key action item:** Verify subagents must run `npm test` exactly once and reuse output (duplicate runs seen in sessions 3 and 4)"}],"totalDurationMs":118654,"totalTokens":37842,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3201,"cache_read_input_tokens":34370,"output_tokens":270,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3201},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
